curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/7267' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM2066", "table_name": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION", "content": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION  The SGM2066 is a negative output charge pump which  has an inside adjustable regulator. The input voltage  range is from 2.7V to 5.5V and the unregulated output  equals to -VIN. For the regulated output of the SGM2066,  the range is from -1.5V to -5V.  The inrush current of the SGM2066 can be decreased  by the internal soft-start circuit. For application case,  four ceramic capacitors and no inductor are required,  and it can be used for supplying optical modules, bias  of RF amplifiers and sensors.  The SGM2066 is available in a Green TDFN-2×2-8AL  package. It operates over an operating temperature  range of -40℃ to +125℃.    "}'
